<div>Because&nbsp;\(E=\frac{V}{d}\), when there is no dielectric filling</div><ul><li>Using the definition&nbsp;\(\frac{Q_0}{A}=\varepsilon_0E\)</li><li>We get&nbsp;\(\frac{Q_0}{A}=\varepsilon_0\frac{V}{d}\)</li><li>\(C_0=\frac{Q_0}{V}=\frac{A\varepsilon_0}{d}\)</li></ul><div>With dielectric, capacitance is increased from&nbsp;\(C_0\)&nbsp;to&nbsp;\(\varepsilon_rC_0\).</div>\[C=\frac{A\varepsilon_0\varepsilon_r}{d}\]